verses.text: Now the sons of Issachar \add were\add*, Tola , and Puah , Jashub , and Shimron , four.

And the sons of Tola ; Uzzi , and Rephaiah , and Jeriel , and Jahmai , and Jibsam , and Shemuel , heads of their father’s house , \add to wit\add*, of Tola : \add they were\add* valiant men of might in their generations ; whose number \add was\add* in the days of David two and twenty thousand and six hundred.
And the sons of Uzzi ; Izrahiah : and the sons of Izrahiah ; Michael , and Obadiah , and Joel , Ishiah , five : all of them chief men.
And with them, by their generations , after the house of their fathers , \add were\add* bands of soldiers for war , six and thirty thousand \add men:\add* for they had many wives and sons.
And their brethren among all the families of Issachar \add were\add* valiant men of might , reckoned in all by their genealogies fourscore and seven thousand. \p
¶ \add The sons\add* of Benjamin ; Bela , and Becher , and Jediael , three.

And the sons of Bela ; Ezbon , and Uzzi , and Uzziel , and Jerimoth , and Iri , five ; heads of the house of \add their\add* fathers , mighty men of valour ; and were reckoned by their genealogies twenty and two thousand and thirty and four.
And the sons of Becher ; Zemira , and Joash , and Eliezer , and Elioenai , and Omri , and Jerimoth , and Abiah , and Anathoth , and Alameth. All these \add are\add* the sons of Becher.
And the number of them, after their genealogy by their generations , heads of the house of their fathers , mighty men of valour , \add was\add* twenty thousand and two hundred.
The sons also of Jediael ; Bilhan : and the sons of Bilhan ; Jeush , and Benjamin , and Ehud , and Chenaanah , and Zethan , and Tharshish , and Ahishahar.

All these the sons of Jediael , by the heads of their fathers , mighty men of valour , \add were\add* seventeen thousand and two hundred \add soldiers\add*, fit to go out for war \add and\add* battle.
Shuppim also, and Huppim , the children of Ir , \add and\add* Hushim , the sons of Aher.\f + \fr 7.12 \ft Ir: or, Iri\f*\f + \fr 7.12 \ft Aher: or, Ahiram\f* \p
¶ The sons of Naphtali ; Jahziel , and Guni , and Jezer , and Shallum , the sons of Bilhah. \p
¶ The sons of Manasseh ; Ashriel , whom she bare : (\add but\add* his concubine the Aramitess bare Machir the father of Gilead :
And Machir took to wife \add the sister\add* of Huppim and Shuppim , whose sister’s name \add was\add* Maachah ;) and the name of the second \add was\add* Zelophehad : and Zelophehad had daughters.
And Maachah the wife of Machir bare a son , and she called his name Peresh ; and the name of his brother \add was\add* Sheresh ; and his sons \add were\add* Ulam and Rakem.
And the sons of Ulam ; Bedan. These \add were\add* the sons of Gilead , the son of Machir , the son of Manasseh.
And his sister Hammoleketh bare Ishod , and Abiezer , and Mahalah.
And the sons of Shemida were, Ahian , and Shechem , and Likhi , and Aniam. \p
¶ And the sons of Ephraim ; Shuthelah , and Bered his son , and Tahath his son , and Eladah his son , and Tahath his son , \p
¶ And Zabad his son , and Shuthelah his son , and Ezer , and Elead , whom the men of Gath \add that were\add* born in \add that\add* land slew , because they came down to take away their cattle.
And Ephraim their father mourned many days , and his brethren came to comfort him. \p
¶ And when he went in to his wife , she conceived , and bare a son , and he called his name Beriah , because it went evil with his house.
(And his daughter \add was\add* Sherah , who built Beth-horon the nether , and the upper , and Uzzen-sherah.)
And Rephah \add was\add* his son , also Resheph , and Telah his son , and Tahan his son ,
Laadan his son , Ammihud his son , Elishama his son ,
Non his son , Jehoshua his son.\f + \fr 7.27 \ft Non: or, Nun\f*\f + \fr 7.27 \ft Jehoshua: or, Joshua\f* \p

¶ And their possessions and habitations \add were\add*, Beth-el and the towns thereof, and eastward Naaran , and westward Gezer , with the towns thereof; Shechem also and the towns thereof, unto Gaza and the towns thereof:\f + \fr 7.28 \ft towns: Heb. daughters\f*\f + \fr 7.28 \ft unto Gaza: or, Adassa\f*

And by the borders of the children of Manasseh , Beth-shean and her towns , Taanach and her towns , Megiddo and her towns , Dor and her towns. In these dwelt the children of Joseph the son of Israel.\f + \fr 7.29 \ft towns: Heb. daughters\f* \p
¶ The sons of Asher ; Imnah , and Isuah , and Ishuai , and Beriah , and Serah their sister.
And the sons of Beriah ; Heber , and Malchiel , who \add is\add* the father of Birzavith.
And Heber begat Japhlet , and Shomer , and Hotham , and Shua their sister.
And the sons of Japhlet ; Pasach , and Bimhal , and Ashvath. These \add are\add* the children of Japhlet.
And the sons of Shamer ; Ahi , and Rohgah , Jehubbah , and Aram.
And the sons of his brother Helem ; Zophah , and Imna , and Shelesh , and Amal.
The sons of Zophah ; Suah , and Harnepher , and Shual , and Beri , and Imrah ,
Bezer , and Hod , and Shamma , and Shilshah , and Ithran , and Beera.
And the sons of Jether ; Jephunneh , and Pispah , and Ara.
And the sons of Ulla ; Arah , and Haniel , and Rezia.

All these \add were\add* the children of Asher , heads of \add their\add* father’s house , choice \add and\add* mighty men of valour , chief of the princes. And the number throughout the genealogy of them that were apt to the war \add and\add* to battle \add was\add* twenty and six thousand men.
